===============================================================================
LINUX COMMANDS IN DEBIAN
===============================================================================

# создать резервную копию существующего файла sources.list: in debian
sudo cp /etc/apt/sources.list /etc/apt/sources.list_backup

# открыть файл sources.list in debian
sudo vim /etc/apt/sources.list

# добавить строку в sources.list с репозиторием backports in debian
deb http://deb.debian.org/debian buster-backports main contrib non-free

# чтобы обновить headers in debian
sudo apt install linux-headers-$(uname -r)

# чтобы проверить ядра in debian
apt search linux-headers

#rsynk docs backup
sudo rsync -aAXv --delete /home/nils/Документы/ /media/nils/PROGS_8GB/DOCS_BACKUP/
sudo rsync -aAXv --delete /home/ /media/nils/WD_Passport/LINUX_BACKUP/

# install deb files
sudo dpkg -i ~/Загрузки/slack-desktop-4.3.2-amd64.deb

# fixes in debian
sudo apt --fix-broken install

#comp parameters
screenfetch
neofetch

#swappiness
#show swappiness
cat /proc/sys/vm/swappiness
#file with swappiness
sudo nano /etc/sysctl.conf
#swappiness parametr in file
vm.swappiness = 10

## just for STEAM 
You might need to specify the right command for games inside Steam.
1.Select a game - that you want to run using your discrete Nvidia card - 
    from the Library page of the Steam client, right-mouse-button-click, 
    and select Properties.
2.Click the "set launch options" button and specify 'optirun %command%' 
    for the command line.
3. Save your changes.
If this doesn't work, try "primusrun" instead of "optirun".

# PYTHON
